commentary: Ali to Shakib Al Hasan, OUT he'll be out stumped here! Bounces back off Buttler's gloves and Shakib is just out of his ground. Was a lovely delivery, spun to beat the edge as he played forward, the bails came off and there was some confusion. Went upstairs, confirmed it wasn't bowled. Buttler didn't glove it but got lucky with the rebound and Shakib couldn't push his foot back over the line. Buttler, himself, wasn't even sure. For a moment I think he thought he'd fluffed it.

commentary: Mashrafe Mortaza to Ali, OUT good grief, that is as soft as a freshly laundered duck-down pillow! Moeen has chipped a catch so tame to mid-on that it might has well have said woof and begged for a doggy-drop on the way down! It was full length, angled into the pads, and he somehow got right underneath his stroke. Mahmudullah merely had to back-pedal two paces
